TYPESCRIPT 
==========
   - extension .ts 
   - run through the TypeScript transcompiler - makes sure its all good
   - output is a .js file, if its all good

************************************
transcompiler - RUN IT - the magic
$ tsc
************************************

once a variable is declared, you cannot change data type 
- boolean, number, null, string, undefined 

const x_var: string = 'abcd'

TS knows 'shapes':
   - knows what methods should or shouldnt be on an object 
   - strings have .length or .toLowerCase()
   - really nice error messages 

type 'ANY': unprotected
   let x_var; 
   // ^^ this is now type 'any'
   x_var = 1;
   x_var = false;

type annotations / declarations:
   let x_var : string; 
   x_var = 'abdc'; 
   x_var = 1234; <<< Error: Type 'number' is not assignable to type 'string'



